     1â†’/**
     2â†’ * Cache Manager with LRU (Least Recently Used) eviction strategy
     3â†’ *
     4â†’ * Provides a thread-safe, configurable caching layer with:
     5â†’ * - LRU eviction when cache reaches max capacity
     6â†’ * - TTL (Time To Live) support for automatic expiration
     7â†’ * - Namespace support for logical grouping
     8â†’ * - Cache statistics tracking
     9â†’ * - Hook system for invalidation events
    10â†’ *
    11â†’ * @example
    12â†’ * ```typescript
    13â†’ * const cache = new CacheManager({ maxSize: 100, ttl: 60000 });
    14â†’ * cache.set('user:123', userData);
    15â†’ * const data = cache.get('user:123');
    16â†’ * cache.invalidate('user:*'); // Invalidate by pattern
    17â†’ * ```
